{"type":"message","id":"0c2bc440","parentId":"20489a68","timestamp":"2026-06-03T07:10:18.685Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it clearly! There's a stash `stash@{0}` that contains the fix. The stash has:\n\n1. `BuildPipeline.cs` - changed `selectedOnly: false` → `true`, plus comment update\n2. Both bat files (`RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat` and `PlatformSwitcher.bat`) - fixed Unity path from `2020.3.49f1c1` to `2020.3.49f1` (without the `c1` suffix)\n3. `RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat` - added `-buildTarget Android` parameter\n4. A bunch of other config changes (package settings, server config, etc.)\n\nSo the stash has both the `selectedOnly: true` fix AND the Unity path fix. The sub-agent correctly applied the Unity path fix but the `selectedOnly` change was also needed.\n\nWait, but when I read the bat file earlier, it already had the correct path `2020.3.49f1-x86_64` (not `2020.3.49f1c1`). So either:\n1. The bat file was modified by the sub-agent\n2. Or someone already fixed it in the working directory\n\nAnd looking at the current `BuildPipeline.cs`, line 114 still shows `selectedOnly: false` (the pre-fix state).\n\nSo what happened is:\n1. The 2026-05-27 fix was stashed (not committed)\n2. The stash was later applied (or partially applied) to fix bat files\n3. But `BuildPipeline.cs`'s `selectedOnly` change from the stash was not applied\n\nThe solution is to apply the stash's fix. But the stash has a LOT of other changes (configs, etc.) that may or may not be desired. Let me just apply the one specific change to BuildPipeline.cs: change `selectedOnly: false` to `selectedOnly: true`.\n\nActually wait - the sub-agent mentioned it \"fixed the Unity path\" - but looking at the current bat file, it already has `2020.3.49f1-x86_64`. So maybe the sub-agent made that change, or maybe it was already there.\n\nLet me just fix the BuildPipeline.cs issue and re-run.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text",